results.name: For n=1 or prime, a(n)=n; otherwise, a(n) is the smallest number not already used which shares a factor with a(n-1).
comment: Since limsup(prime(n)) is infinity, it is easy to see that the sequence contains all even numbers. So it is natural to conjecture that the sequence is a permutation of the positive integers.
link: Peter J. C. Moses, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..1000
